Robe to complete my Ragebringer, so I went to check out his spawn. In the various guides around, it is usually stated that you have to kill the ph's until the brigand spawns, then wait for the brigand to despawn at 8pm, to be replaced by Mr. Small at 10pm. It is implied and in some cases stated, that this can be a time consuming process. I went through 5 cycles (4.5 EQ days) and found that the brigand and Vilnius spawned every time.<br>
<br>
Just wanted to point this out for any rogues nearing this step.<br>
<br>
PS. As a bonus, I am amiable to parts of Qeynos (DE rogue), and somewhat richer, thanks to a couple backpacks of bandit sashes. I also finished the Hobbitt while watching the cycle, hehe.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhinterdir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HinterDir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/02 4:40:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3782.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vilnius the Small</span><hr size=1> there is no ph on the brigand.<br>
he will spawn in that same position every time the cycle gets to him.<br>
he does wander off *sometimes* due to chain agroing on animals.<br>
if he is not at his spawnpoint when he despawns he will not trigger Vilnius.<br>
if he gets killed before he despawns he will not trigger Vilnius.<br>
if he is not there you might have to wait for this cycle to finish and the bandit respawning thus starting the cycle again.<br>
this might take some hours.<br>
if you are not beeing secret about that you wait for Vilnius, he will agro on you forcing you to kill him or train him to zone, not triggering Vilnius.<br>
<br>
no secret PH or routine to trigger him.<br>
just patience <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujaedengrae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaeden Grae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/02 7:48:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3782.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vilnius the Small</span><hr size=1> I think what Saev is saying is that the brigand was always up and always cycled to Vil.  I found the same when I did my roe, the brigand and Vil were up for two days through a patch, I didn't have to kill anything.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaagiquickhands.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maagi Quickhands</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/13/02 10:23:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3782.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vilnius the Small</span><hr size=1> Ok, right now I'm still confused about this, after trying to it for 3 hours. So few questions:<br>
<br>
We got a brigand spawn in 3 different places. In spot where is 4 bandits (if you look up to hill from camp, it's on your left, far left downhill), on hill (someone bloody killed him), one in camp, and one again on the &quot;semi-camp&quot; to left. So overall 4 times, 3 times in different places.<br>
<br>
What is difference between these spots?<br>
Does only the one on hill work?<br>
<br>
Runner : I've read guides saying I should kill and kill over again runner from &quot;main&quot; camp, who runs to hill (and apparently, stops on hill). Is this so? and does it matter when I kill this bandit (they don't dash right away, they stand a while)?<br>
What about odd thing, that we've been having two runners in same time, is this a bug or just bad timing?<br>
What about those two bandits, who patrol around main camp, go somewhere, come to that &quot;camp&quot; on left, and back to maincamp. Are they anything important?<br>
<br>
What to do with all bandits? Do I leave them be, or kill everyone (we got all spawns just by killing every bandit nearby)?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usaevanjnoir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saevan JNoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/13/02 10:59:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3782.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vilnius the Small</span><hr size=1> The only brigand you need to worry about is right at the top of the hill, above the hill camp (not the bandit farm, if that is confusing you). What I was trying to say was that there were no ph's and there was no runner involved. <br>
<br>
In the several cycles I watched, the brigand popped in the right place and stayed there until 8pm EQ time, when he disappeared. At 10pm Vilnius spawned, and in turn disappeared at 6am. The only time the brigand left his spot was to kill bears etc. but he always returned (except when he agroed on me the first time).<br>
<br>
Ignore the other bandits and brigands, or kill them for faction and sashes (cash and faction in Qeynos). <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=3782.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=3782.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3782.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3782.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3782.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3782.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3782.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesaf